cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with domain adaptation in deep neural networks for image segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of stacked autoencoders and systematic dropout also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques for training the neural network (cs.NE) and evaluation of performance metrics (cs.IR).
